regredienti: dative of reference ; on his way back.

4. iuventus: they alone escaped from the slaughter, swam across the Eder‚ which here flows nearly east, and at this stream resisted the Roman advance.

Adranam: now the Eder (a branch of the Fulda, which it joins near Cassel), a little east of north of the Taunus.
